\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Fixed-dwell reconstruction quality of the global power knob:\ \textsc  {RIDGE-SCAT32} against balanced \textsc  {SCAT32-060} at $\nu =2000$, seed $0$ (the centrepiece of the operating-point primary). Each row shows, left to right, the ground truth, the \textsc  {SCAT32-060} reconstruction ($\bar  {\rho }=0.60$), and the \textsc  {RIDGE-SCAT32} reconstruction ($\bar  {\rho }^{*}\approx 22$), annotated with the per-row $\Delta Q$ badge:\ the median-$\Delta Q$ scene \texttt  {m1\_chirp\_3} (radiometric $\mathrm  {PSNR}_{\mathrm  {rad}}$ of $9.4$ and $10.9$~dB, respectively; $\Delta Q=+1.5$~dB), the best-$\Delta Q$ scene \texttt  {m1\_maze\_1} ($28.7$ and $35.4$~dB; $\Delta Q=+6.7$~dB), and the worst-$\Delta Q$ scene \texttt  {m1\_contour\_1}, a contour ($13.6$ and $7.7$~dB; $\Delta Q=-5.8$~dB). The right panel plots the per-image $\Delta Q$ (seed-mean over five seeds) for all $24$ confirmatory scenes grouped by family; the solid line is the campaign median $1.87$~dB, the dashed line the $1.0$~dB operating bar, and $19/24$ scenes exceed zero. $\mathrm  {PSNR}_{\mathrm  {rad}}$ denotes the radiometric peak signal-to-noise ratio and $\Delta Q=\mathrm  {PSNR}_{\mathrm  {rad}} (\textsc  {RIDGE-SCAT32})-\mathrm  {PSNR}_{\mathrm  {rad}}(\textsc  {SCAT32-060})$; the thumbnail values are the seed-$0$ realization. The colour is used only for display purposes, and each row shares a common grayscale scale.}}{14}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:actiii-main}{{2}{14}{Fixed-dwell reconstruction quality of the global power knob:\^^M\textsc {RIDGE-SCAT32} against balanced \textsc {SCAT32-060} at $\nu =2000$, seed $0$ (the centrepiece of the operating-point primary). Each row shows, left to right, the ground truth, the \textsc {SCAT32-060} reconstruction ($\rhobar =0.60$), and the \textsc {RIDGE-SCAT32} reconstruction ($\rhobar ^{*}\approx 22$), annotated with the per-row $\Delta Q$ badge:\ the median-$\Delta Q$ scene \texttt {m1\_chirp\_3} (radiometric $\mathrm {PSNR}_{\mathrm {rad}}$ of $9.4$ and $10.9$~dB, respectively; $\Delta Q=+1.5$~dB), the best-$\Delta Q$ scene \texttt {m1\_maze\_1} ($28.7$ and $35.4$~dB; $\Delta Q=+6.7$~dB), and the worst-$\Delta Q$ scene \texttt {m1\_contour\_1}, a contour ($13.6$ and $7.7$~dB; $\Delta Q=-5.8$~dB). The right panel plots the per-image $\Delta Q$ (seed-mean over five seeds) for all $24$ confirmatory scenes grouped by family; the solid line is the campaign median $1.87$~dB, the dashed line the $1.0$~dB operating bar, and $19/24$ scenes exceed zero. $\mathrm {PSNR}_{\mathrm {rad}}$ denotes the radiometric peak signal-to-noise ratio and $\Delta Q=\mathrm {PSNR}_{\mathrm {rad}} (\textsc {RIDGE-SCAT32})-\mathrm {PSNR}_{\mathrm {rad}}(\textsc {SCAT32-060})$; the thumbnail values are the seed-$0$ realization. The colour is used only for display purposes, and each row shares a common grayscale scale}{figure.2}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Act III design doctrine:\ information rewards scene-adapted geometry, uniform dose alone does not eliminate that headroom (development evidence, panels~a--b), the conditioning stack defines the deployable class tested by the full-stack certificate (panel~c), and global operating-point control survives orthogonally (panel~e; the operating-point reconstructions are Figure~\ref {fig:actiii-main}). (a)~Guard collapse of the adaptive \textsc  {OED-DT} mixture along the descending exact-rounding path for the development glyph scene at the fast anchor ($\nu =2000$, $b=0.60$); development-only evidence, not a confirmatory endpoint. The dose deviation $\max |d/\bar  d-1|$ (orange), the spectral floor $\mu _{\min }$ (green), and the A-risk ratio $\mathrm  {tr}(V^{-1})/ \mathrm  {tr}(V_{\mathrm  {fix}}^{-1})$ (blue) are shown versus the path-specific OED fraction $\alpha =m/972$, with the dashed guard bars the $\pm 5\%$ dose band ($0.05$), the spectral floor ($0.5\times $), and the A-risk cap ($1.05\times $), respectively; every $\alpha >0$ exceeds the dose band by $2$--$11\times $ and, by $\alpha \approx 0.06$, breaches the spectral floor, while the A-risk cap never binds and only the balanced endpoint $\alpha =0$ is dose-feasible (failing the separate efficiency floor $\mathrm  {eff}_D\ge 0.95$), so \texttt  {PATH\_FEASIBLE\_ALPHA} is \textsc  {None} (\texttt  {NO\_FEASIBLE\_POINT\_ON\_PATH}). (b)~Constructive dose-only geometry headroom over the six development families; development-only lower bound, not a confirmatory endpoint or population estimate. The per-dimension dose-only primal gap $[\log \det V(\xi )-\log \det V_{\mathrm  {SCAT32}}]/r$ within the $\pm 5\%$ dose band is shown at anchor~A ($\nu =2000$, $b=0.60$; circles) and anchor~B ($\nu =200$, $b=0.05$; diamonds), the right axis reporting the D-efficiency lower bound $\exp (\mathrm  {gap})$; across glyph, chirp, maze, spokes, contour, and microtexture the gaps are $0.78$, $0.86$, $0.59$, $0.90$, $0.90$, and $0.92$ at anchor~A and $0.90$, $0.50$, $0.51$, $0.79$, $0.59$, and $0.72$ at anchor~B, respectively (D-efficiency lower bounds $1.6$--$2.5\times $). The construction is support-preserving and establishes existence, not the dose-only optimum. (c)~Confirmatory \texttt  {FULL\_STACK\_CERT} certificate distribution under the fallback-descriptive branch ($0/480$ \texttt  {CERTIFIED}). The left bars give the terminal status of the $480$ certificate cells split by the four $(\nu ,b)$ anchors ($120$ cells each):\ at $(\nu 200,b0.05)$, $(\nu 200,b0.60)$, $(\nu 2000,b0.05)$, and $(\nu 2000,b0.60)$ the cells are $77$, $67$, $84$, and $71$ \texttt  {COUNTEREXAMPLE} and $43$, $53$, $36$, and $49$ \texttt  {NUMERICAL\_UNRESOLVED}, respectively, with no \texttt  {CERTIFIED} cell; the right panel is the empirical cumulative distribution of the finite primal gap per dimension for the $299$ \texttt  {COUNTEREXAMPLE} cells (median $1.43$), the dashed line the near-optimality bar $G_{\mathrm  {stack}}/r\le 10^{-2}$, which every counterexample exceeds by about two orders of magnitude. The certificate is reported descriptively and no categorical near-optimality claim is made. (e)~Conjugate-corners operating doctrine for the global power knob:\ the plane is spanned by the optical-power/flux budget (horizontal) and the acquisition-time budget (vertical); in the photon-budgeted corner (low power, ample time; Q90 count-time secondary) the balanced \textsc  {SCAT32-060} design with the full-stack certificate is preferred and \texttt  {RIDGE\_SPEED\_PASS} is \textsc  {false}, whereas in the time-limited, power-available corner (ample power, little time; fixed-dwell quality primary) the ridge operating point $\bar  {\rho }^{*}$ delivers a $+1.87$~dB median gain and \texttt  {RIDGE\_OPERATING\_PASS} is \textsc  {true}, with the curved arrow marking the single global power knob that moves the system between the two corners. The colour is used only for display purposes.}}{15}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:actiii}{{3}{15}{Act III design doctrine:\ information rewards scene-adapted geometry, uniform dose alone does not eliminate that headroom (development evidence, panels~a--b), the conditioning stack defines the deployable class tested by the full-stack certificate (panel~c), and global operating-point control survives orthogonally (panel~e; the operating-point reconstructions are Figure~\ref {fig:actiii-main}). (a)~Guard collapse of the adaptive \textsc {OED-DT} mixture along the descending exact-rounding path for the development glyph scene at the fast anchor ($\nu =2000$, $b=0.60$); development-only evidence, not a confirmatory endpoint. The dose deviation $\max |d/\bar d-1|$ (orange), the spectral floor $\mu _{\min }$ (green), and the A-risk ratio $\mathrm {tr}(V^{-1})/ \mathrm {tr}(V_{\mathrm {fix}}^{-1})$ (blue) are shown versus the path-specific OED fraction $\alpha =m/972$, with the dashed guard bars the $\pm 5\%$ dose band ($0.05$), the spectral floor ($0.5\times $), and the A-risk cap ($1.05\times $), respectively; every $\alpha >0$ exceeds the dose band by $2$--$11\times $ and, by $\alpha \approx 0.06$, breaches the spectral floor, while the A-risk cap never binds and only the balanced endpoint $\alpha =0$ is dose-feasible (failing the separate efficiency floor $\mathrm {eff}_D\ge 0.95$), so \texttt {PATH\_FEASIBLE\_ALPHA} is \textsc {None} (\texttt {NO\_FEASIBLE\_POINT\_ON\_PATH}). (b)~Constructive dose-only geometry headroom over the six development families; development-only lower bound, not a confirmatory endpoint or population estimate. The per-dimension dose-only primal gap $[\log \det V(\xi )-\log \det V_{\mathrm {SCAT32}}]/r$ within the $\pm 5\%$ dose band is shown at anchor~A ($\nu =2000$, $b=0.60$; circles) and anchor~B ($\nu =200$, $b=0.05$; diamonds), the right axis reporting the D-efficiency lower bound $\exp (\mathrm {gap})$; across glyph, chirp, maze, spokes, contour, and microtexture the gaps are $0.78$, $0.86$, $0.59$, $0.90$, $0.90$, and $0.92$ at anchor~A and $0.90$, $0.50$, $0.51$, $0.79$, $0.59$, and $0.72$ at anchor~B, respectively (D-efficiency lower bounds $1.6$--$2.5\times $). The construction is support-preserving and establishes existence, not the dose-only optimum. (c)~Confirmatory \texttt {FULL\_STACK\_CERT} certificate distribution under the fallback-descriptive branch ($0/480$ \texttt {CERTIFIED}). The left bars give the terminal status of the $480$ certificate cells split by the four $(\nu ,b)$ anchors ($120$ cells each):\ at $(\nu 200,b0.05)$, $(\nu 200,b0.60)$, $(\nu 2000,b0.05)$, and $(\nu 2000,b0.60)$ the cells are $77$, $67$, $84$, and $71$ \texttt {COUNTEREXAMPLE} and $43$, $53$, $36$, and $49$ \texttt {NUMERICAL\_UNRESOLVED}, respectively, with no \texttt {CERTIFIED} cell; the right panel is the empirical cumulative distribution of the finite primal gap per dimension for the $299$ \texttt {COUNTEREXAMPLE} cells (median $1.43$), the dashed line the near-optimality bar $G_{\mathrm {stack}}/r\le 10^{-2}$, which every counterexample exceeds by about two orders of magnitude. The certificate is reported descriptively and no categorical near-optimality claim is made. (e)~Conjugate-corners operating doctrine for the global power knob:\ the plane is spanned by the optical-power/flux budget (horizontal) and the acquisition-time budget (vertical); in the photon-budgeted corner (low power, ample time; Q90 count-time secondary) the balanced \textsc {SCAT32-060} design with the full-stack certificate is preferred and \texttt {RIDGE\_SPEED\_PASS} is \textsc {false}, whereas in the time-limited, power-available corner (ample power, little time; fixed-dwell quality primary) the ridge operating point $\rhobar ^{*}$ delivers a $+1.87$~dB median gain and \texttt {RIDGE\_OPERATING\_PASS} is \textsc {true}, with the curved arrow marking the single global power knob that moves the system between the two corners. The colour is used only for display purposes}{figure.3}{}}
